  <title>Change board size</title>
    <p>To change the board:</p>
     <list>
       <item><p>Click <guiseq><gui>Settings</gui><gui>Preferences</gui></guiseq></p></item>
     </list>

    <p>The <gui>Board Size</gui> section lets you to select a small, medium or large board. While a board with larger size gives you more space, it also places more objects on the board per turn.</p>

  <section id="board-parameters">
    <p>The 3 different board sizes have the following parameters:</p>

    <table shade="all">
     <tr>
       <td><p><em>Size</em></p></td> <td><p><em>Width</em></p></td><td><p><em>Height</em></p></td>
       <td><p><em>Number of types</em></p></td> <td><p><em>New objects per turn</em></p></td><td><p><em>Number of cells</em></p></td>
     </tr>>
     <tr>
    <td><p>Small</p></td> <td><p>7</p></td><td><p>7</p></td>>
    <td><p>5</p></td> <td><p>3</p></td><td><p>49</p></td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td><p>Medium</p></td> <td><p>9</p></td><td><p>9</p></td>
    <td><p>7</p></td> <td><p>3</p></td><td><p>81</p></td>
  </tr>
<tr>
<td><p>Large</p></td> <td><p>20</p></td><td><p>15</p></td>
    <td><p>7</p></td> <td><p>7</p></td><td><p>300</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</section>





